<p>Later the 3rd left Vermozelle, &amp; after two days in Caestre left for the Somme after the 1st, whom I saw on the train. They landed <strike>at</strike> near Amiens, &amp; went through some bombing experiences, -- losing Birch of the transport who was killed, &amp; several wounded including <strike>Billy Roscoe</strike> . Heisman of [indecipherable] party.<br/>After this they returned north, &amp; <strike>afte</strike> their train on the way to Hazebrouck</p>
